 📊 InternSpark Python Internship – Task 3

 Data Analysis Project using Pandas

This project was developed as part of the **InternSpark Python Programming Internship**.

 📌 Project Title

**Student Performance Data Analysis**

 🎯 Objective

Analyze a student dataset using Pandas by cleaning the data, performing filtering and grouping operations, generating summary statistics, creating visualizations, and extracting meaningful insights.

---

 🛠 Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Pandas
- Matplotlib

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
data_analysis_project/
│── data_analysis.py
│── student_data.csv
│── requirements.txt
│── README.md
│── sample_output.txt
│── cleaned_student_data.csv
│── department_average_marks.png
│── department_distribution.png
```

---

 ✨ Features

- Load CSV dataset using Pandas
- Clean missing values
- Remove duplicate records
- Generate summary statistics
- Filter students with marks greater than 80
- Group students by department
- Calculate average marks by department
- Generate Bar Chart
- Generate Pie Chart
- Save cleaned dataset

---

 📊 Dataset

The dataset contains the following columns:

- Student_ID
- Name
- Department
- Gender
- Marks
- Attendance

---

 ▶️ How to Run

 Install Required Packages

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

or

```bash
pip install pandas matplotlib
```

 Run the Project

```bash
python data_analysis.py
```

---

 📈 Output

The program displays:

- Original Dataset
- Missing Values
- Summary Statistics
- Students with Marks > 80
- Average Marks by Department

It also generates:

- Bar Chart (Average Marks by Department)
- Pie Chart (Students by Department)

---

 📁 Generated Files

After execution, the following files are created:

- cleaned_student_data.csv
- department_average_marks.png
- department_distribution.png

